      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "Wide open. CAPTAIN CAM (1) is racing g well and may be value. Scored this grade here last time over 1150m but fitter again and has a good record over the longer trip. Can measure up again. ADACHI (3) went back to the tail and charged late to finish seventh at Hobart last time. Run was much better than it looked. Has a great record this course and distance and can improve sharply.  TIKKEN (5) did well to score two back then placed over 1350m at this track, beaten 0.9 lengths latest. Should be thereabouts. TUSKEGEE (2) was a winner here before a break but returns on the back of a trial win and placed 2/2 when fresh. STAR TERRITORY (7) raced on speed before fading latest here. Strong record with Kelvin Sanderson in the irons, including a win. Best form puts him right in this.",
